  "prompt": "Why is The Sandman called 'sandman'?",
  "response": "The Sandman is called 'sandman' based on folklore and mythology. The name comes from the traditional European mythological character who is said to sprinkle sand or dust into people's eyes to bring sleep and cause them to have dreams. In Neil Gaiman's comic book series \"The Sandman,\" the protagonist, also known as Morpheus, Dream, or Oneiros, governs the realm of dreams and embodies the concept of dreaming. The title emphasizes the connection to sleep, dreams, and the ancient stories surrounding the Sandman figure.",
